<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17074] Not correctly escaped quote in bin/solr script</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17074</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In solr/script file a quote is not escaped&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;echo &quot; &#160;-force &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;If attempting to start Solr as the root user, the script will exit with a warning that running Solr as &quot;root&quot; can cause problems.&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; echo &quot; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;It is possible to override this warning with the `-force` parameter.&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First issue : &#160;double quote arround &quot;root&quot; should be escaped \&quot;root\&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second issue : single quote around -force should be standard quote.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solr script try to evaluate -force and the output is&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&#160;-force &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;If attempting to start Solr as the root user, the script will exit with a warning that running Solr as root can cause problems.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;/opt/solr-9.3.0/bin/solr: line 418: -force: command not found&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; It is possible to override this warning with the &#160;parameter.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
